## Battle-Metrics | Shroud Player Card
A responsive, single-page web application that displays PUBG player statistics (featuring Shroud's demo stats) with interactive documentation, FAQ, and system status panels. Built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

## Table of Contents
Overview

Features

Demo Data

File Structure

Installation & Usage

LocalStorage Caching

## Overview
Battle-Metrics is a front-end demo application that simulates fetching PUBG API player statistics. It showcases:

// A beautifully styled player stats card for "Shroud"

// Collapsible documentation and FAQ panels

// Real-time system status monitoring

// Persistent data storage using browser localStorage

// Fully responsive layout for mobile and desktop

## Features
Player Card

// Displays lifetime solo stats: kills, wins, top 10s, damage dealt, rounds played

// Specialized metrics: longest kill distance, walk distance, ride distance

Note: Shroud's ride distance is exactly 0m (no vehicle usage - edge case accuracy)

## Interactive Panels
// Documentation - API reference, endpoint details, integration guide

// FAQ - Common questions about the demo and functionality

// Status - Live system metrics including localStorage status and sync times



## Demo Data
The application uses static mock data representing Shroud's statistics:

javascript
{
    name: "Shroud",
    playerId: "account.d50fdc18fcad49c691d38466bed6f8fd",
    kills: 3,
    wins: 0,
    top10s: 0,
    damageDealt: 300,
    roundsPlayed: 1,
    longestKill: 76.34484,
    walkDistance: 99.900154,
    rideDistance: 0  // Exact zero value - no vehicle usage
}


##  LocalStorage Caching
// How It Works

// After clicking "Get Player Info", the player data and timestamp are saved to localStorage

// On page load, the application checks for saved data and restores the card

The "Clear Saved Data" button removes both shroudPlayerCard and lastShroudViewTimestamp keys

// Storage Keys
// Key	Purpose
// shroudPlayerCard	Stores player data and display timestamp
// lastShroudViewTimestamp	Stores ISO timestamp of last view
// Benefits
Reduces "API calls" in a real implementation


 ## Customization
// Replace with Real PUBG API
// To connect to the actual PUBG Developer API:

// Obtain an API key from PUBG Developer Portal

// Modify displayShroudCard() to fetch real player data

// Update the stats mapping to match PUBG API response structure






